But this is not immediately clear when the proposed regulations are read on their own. Experts have taken issue with other aspects of the proposed regulations, such as their poor wording and inconsistencies. Ambiguous rules, particularly for health and COVID-19, can harm public trust and provide fertile ground for misinformation.